      serialVersionUID:
      1833476829524121758L

      • Serialized Fields

        • image

          com.jogamp.opengl.util.texture.TextureData image
          Contains the image file which will be bound and drawn later on.

        • tileCoord

          IntegerVector3D tileCoord
          Refers to the position in "tile coordinates". Tile coordinates are described in the slippy map convention. Let (x,y,z) be the components of the Vector3D class, then they're semantics are as follows: x stands for the x-coordinate of the tile resource. y stands for the y-coordinate of the tile resource. z stands for the zoom coordinate, referring from the TileState class.

        • style

          Style style
          The style of this tile.

      serialVersionUID:
      701077077353252427L

      • Serialized Fields

        • lat

          float lat
          Latitude coordinate which this weather information refers to. It is fix when the object is created.

        • lon

          float lon
          Longitude coordinate which this weather information refers to. It is fix when the object is created.

        • temperatur

          float temperatur
          Current temperature at the place, where this WeatherResource refers to in degree Celsius. Other measures are not supported.

        • name

          java.lang.String name
          Name of the place where this WeatherResource object refers to.

        • key

          java.lang.String key

        • weatherConditionCode

          int weatherConditionCode
          The weatherConditionCode is a openweathermap.org specific code, that indicates the current weather status in a qualitative way (e.g. "moderate rain"). Each weather condition code refers also to an icon.
          See Also:
          Weather Condition Codes

        • icon

          java.awt.Image icon
          Depends on the weatherConditionCode variable. The icon is drawn in the view later on.
          See Also:
          weatherConditionCode

        • textureData

          com.jogamp.opengl.util.texture.TextureData textureData
          The final "image" that represents one WeatherResource. TextureData object in order to easy paintable by OpenGL.
